Robert Clark was a prisoner of war during the Second World War . 
  He survived the Nazi ‘death march’ and is blind and deaf . 
  96-year-old has used savings to pay for a live-in carer . 
  More than 127,000 people have signed petition to allow him to stay in his home . 
  Brent Council has refused to increase funding for his carer and says he is not a special case . 
  Mr Clark could be forced out of his home and into a care home . 
 